# Post-Deploy Browser Review

After every commit pushed to `main`, use the browser tool to review the live site at **https://www.internode-ai.com**.

## Required checks

For each active campaign slug in `src/config/campaigns.ts`, visit `https://www.internode-ai.com/lp/<slug>` and verify:

1. **Page loads** — no blank screen, no error overlay, HTTP 200
2. **Hero section** — headline, subheadline, and CTA button are visible and styled correctly
3. **All sections render** — scroll through pain-points, features, social-proof, FAQ, final-CTA, and footer
4. **CTA button** — present and links to the correct `cta.href` from the campaign config
5. **Dark/light mode** — background and text colours match `theme.darkMode` from the campaign config
6. **No console errors** — check browser console for JS exceptions or failed network requests
7. **PostHog proxy** — at least one request to `/ingest/...` appears in the Network tab (not blocked)

## How to run the review

```
1. Wait ~60 s after push for Vercel to finish deploying (or confirm via Vercel dashboard)
2. Open https://www.internode-ai.com — should show the campaign index page
3. Click each campaign link and run the checklist above
4. Report any visual regressions, broken sections, or console errors found
```

## What to report

If any check fails, surface it immediately with:
- The affected URL
- A screenshot or description of the issue
- The likely cause (recent config change, CSS regression, etc.)

Do **not** mark a deployment complete until the browser review passes.
